Nigerian singer, Wizkid has stated that he, Davido, and Burna Boy are “scratching the surface” even at the peak of their music career.  In an interview with ARISE TV, the Grammy award winner urged up and coming Nigerian artistes to take the country’s music industry to a higher level. He further said that he believes that up and coming artistes will do better in taking the Nigerian music Industry above and beyond, adding that nothing is impossible. “Nothing is impossible. You know you can really take it above and beyond. We are just scratching the surface; me, Burna, and David. ”I believe the next generation will take it to the next level because we are still like learners. “All we do is inspiring the young people, showing them that everything is possible by doing what you have to do,” he said. Recall that Burna boy and Wizkid recently won their first Grammy Awards. Burnaboy won the award for the Best Global Music Album ‘Twice as Tall’ while Wizkid won Best music video for ‘Brown Skin Girl’ with Beyoncé. Popular Nigerian singer, Davido has congratulated his colleagues, Burna Boy and Wizkid as they both bagged a Grammy award last night. The 28-year-old singer reacted to Burna Boy and Wizkid wins hours after the 63rd edition of the awards ceremony hosted by Trevor Noah on Sunday, March 14, in the… In "Entertainment" Grammy awards winners, Burna Boy and Wizkid have been nominated for the Best International Act at the BET Award Show for 2021. Burna Boy won the category in the last two years and Wizkid won it in 2012, when the category had two divisions for Africa and the UK. Earlier… In "Entertainment" By Joshua Olomu Abuja - Nigerian Afro-fusion singer, Damini Ogulu, better known as Burna Boy, has lost the Best World Music Album trophy to Beninese ace singer, Angélique Kidjo, at the 62nd Grammy Award. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the 62nd Annual Grammy Awards ceremony, acclaimed to… In "Entertainment"